---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Portugal Airport Rental Guides | TripAxle"
  description="Understand pickup locations, shuttle desks, returns, and common rental issues at Portugal’s main airports."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Airport rental guides</p>
    <h1>Airport Rental Guides for Portugal</h1>
    <p class="intro">
  Use these guides to understand pickup locations, shuttle desks, returns,
  and common airport rental issues in Lisbon, Porto, and Faro before you reserve.
  </p>
  </section>

  <section class="airport-grid">
    <article class="airport-card">
      <h2>Lisbon Airport</h2>
      <p>
  A common pickup point for travelers leaving the city quickly, though not always necessary for city-only stays.
    </p>
      <a href="/lisbon-airport-car-rental">Lisbon Airport guide →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="airport-card">
      <h2>Porto Airport</h2>
      <p>
  A practical starting point for northern Portugal road trips and flexible
  multi-stop itineraries.
  </p>
      <a href="/porto-airport-car-rental">Porto Airport guide →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="airport-card">
      <h2>Faro Airport</h2>
      <p>
        Often the key pickup point for Algarve trips, beach stays, and southern
        Portugal driving routes.
      </p>
      <a href="/faro-airport-car-rental">Faro Airport guide →</a>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="content-grid">
    <article class="main-card">
      <h2>What these airport guides will cover</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Where pickup desks or shuttle transfers are usually located</li>
        <li>Common pickup and return issues to watch for</li>
        <li>How each airport may fit different trip plans and arrival times</li>
        <li>What to check before choosing airport pickup over city pickup</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How to use this hub</h2>
      <p>
       Start with the airport that matches your arrival city. Then use the
       guide to decide whether airport pickup, city pickup, or no rental at all
       makes the most sense for your trip.
      </p>
    </article>

    <aside class="side-card">
      <h2>Airport guides</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Lisbon Airport car rental guide</li>
        <li>Porto Airport car rental guide</li>
        <li>Faro Airport car rental guide</li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <style>
    .hero {
      padding: 2rem 0 2.25rem;
      max-width: 760px;
    }

    .eyebrow {
      margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
      color: #2f6fed;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    }

    h1 {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: clamp(2.1rem, 5vw, 3.6rem);
      line-height: 1.08;
    }

    .intro {
      margin-top: 1rem;
      color: #5b5b55;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      max-width: 680px;
    }

    .airport-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .airport-card,
    .main-card,
    .side-card {
      background: white;
      border: 1px solid #e4e4de;
      border-radius: 16px;
      padding: 1.25rem;
    }

    .airport-card h2,
    .main-card h2,
    .side-card h2 {
      margin-top: 0;
    }

    .airport-card p {
      color: #5b5b55;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    .airport-card a {
      font-weight: 600;
      color: #2f6fed;
    }

    .content-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    ul {
      padding-left: 1.2rem;
    }

    li + li {
      margin-top: 0.5rem;
    }

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .airport-grid,
      .content-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>